One of the requirements by the State of Florida to apply for a concealed weapons permit is to have successfully taken a concealed carry course under a certified instructor. Miami Shooters Club provides such a course with its team of NRA certified instructors - who will teach students the important fundamentals of how to safely use a semi-automatic pistol and revolver. Your concealed weapons permit will allow you to concealed carry in more than 30 states.

Miami Shooters Club's instructors carry multiple certifications under the NRA, have traveled abroad to train and receive firearm certifications, and are hand-to-hand self defense experts - having taught multiple seminars for the Miami Dade Police Department. Under their instruction in the concealed carry class, students will learn the mechanisms behind pistols and how they operate while learning how to grip the firearm, aim, pull the trigger, get into a proper stance, and much more. The class also covers many of the legal issues and expected ethics of concealed carry in Florida. The classes are designed for complete beginners who have never touched a gun before... but experienced shooters will learn something as well.

At the end of the classroom portion, students will safely discharge a pistol under the supervision of a certified instructor, as required by the State of Florida. Miami Shooters Club will provide a firearm, ammunition, eye protection, and ear protection at no extra cost.

Classes take place in Miami on Fridays at 6:30pm or on Saturdays at 1pm.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Marlin XL7 .25-06
postcontent:
Selling a barely used, mint condition Marlin XL7 in .25-06. If that's not a cartridge you've ever heard of, it's essentially a .25 or 7mm bullet in a .30-06 casing. Less recoil, higher velocity, flatter trajectory. Considered by many to be the perfect round for whitetail. 

The rifle is blued with a black synthetic stock. Bought new I think about five or six years ago? Maybe a few more. I can't quite recall. I bought it as a hunting rifle and never found a buck with it. Started taking a 336C in .35 with me instead and got a buck every time. Maybe this rifle is cursed...but maybe I shouldn't say that if I'm trying to sell it? The good news is it's only ever been fired a few times to sight in the scope and then once every season to be sure it held its zero.

It is an accurate rifle for the price for sure. It's currently wearing a Nikon Prostaff 9X scope--a $150 scope, if I recall. This could either be included or not, but it's currently priced as if included. Comes with one box, 20 rounds of high grade Hornady hunting ammo.

The other thing I'm told is worth mentioning is it was made just before the Remington corporate takeover that apparently turned Marlin's quality control to shit. The barrel is marked JM, accordingly.

Price negotiable. Might trade. Am in the market for a pocket pistol.

title: For Sale:  Saiga 308-  Izhmash (Russian made and no longer legal for import)
postcontent:
If you are looking at this ad then you probably know that there will be no more of these imported into the US and it truly a collectors item. My Saiga 12's sold very quickly and one I was told is going to be put away in a safe for many, many years. 

Here is you chance to by a new, in the original box/plastic, import banned Saiga 308 Caliber Semi-Auto Rifle. It has a 16.34” barrel, 10 round magazine (it may be an 8 round mag, I have never loaded it to check), chrome lined barrel; sling mounts, cleaning kit, cleaning rod, oil bottle, matte black finish with a black polymer forearm and stock. 

I will also make available to the buyer only, NATO 308 ammo (this is the good, kick butt ammo with the NATO stamp) 147gr for 60 cents a round, 200 rounds total). This rifle is extremely accurate out of the box and will make an excellent hunting (with proper mag), 3-gun, sporting or collectors rifle.

If you live out of state I will ship to your FFL for the cost of the rifle and shipping. Shipping charge will be the actual shipping charge. Your FFL must be willing to receive from a non-FFL. FFL to FFL will incur additional charges.

If you live in the state of KY I can sell to you FTF. You must:
1). Be willing to meet face to face and pay cash. 
2). Be willing to provide a valid form of govt ID (drivers license or passport).
3). Legally able to purchase a firearm.
